From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 13:26:45 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(e2e): add OverlayBase.get_e2e_playwright_args hook for
 per-spec config selection

The external runner builds the npx playwright command with no way for an
overlay to inject per-spec Playwright flags. A multi-config Playwright suite
(one config per lane, api-flow vs contrib vs portal) needs the right
-c config chosen by the spec, which the overlay knows and core does not.

Add get_e2e_playwright_args(spec_path) -> list[str] (default empty, the
args-sibling of get_e2e_env_extras) and thread it into the external runner
command ahead of any explicit --playwright-args (caller override still wins).
The empty default preserves every existing overlay/run unchanged.

## Configuration
No config. New overlay hook defaults to an empty list; overlays opt in by
overriding it.
