sive with `--manifest`). Pure render/merge lives in `_test_plan_render`, host orchestration in `_test_plan`.
+- Core has no Playwright suite (no UI). Overlays declare their own via `get_e2e_config()`; `t3 <overlay> e2e {run,external,project}` runs them. The `external` runner resolves its Playwright working dir in order ([#2620](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2620)): an explicit `--repo` (a `[e2e_repos.<name>]` clone) wins; else, when `get_e2e_config()` supplies BOTH a `url` and a `ref` (`overlay_e2e_repo` lifts them into an `E2ERepo`, `e2e_dir` default `e2e`), the overlay's own repo is cloned at that ref (a `--branch`/`--ref` override wins) — so a migrated suite on an unmerged branch runs without a separate `T3_PRIVATE_TESTS` checkout; else the legacy `T3_PRIVATE_TESTS` directory. A green/red `e2e run` records run provenance on the durable recipe (`Ticket.extra['e2e_recipe'].last_run`, `core/e2e_workitem.record_run`): result + per-repo SHAs + env, plus (for vanilla-spec suites whose specs live in another repo, [#272](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/272)) the exact `spec_path` and the overlay-resolved `manifest_entry` id (its CI lane) via the `get_e2e_run_provenance(spec_path)` overlay hook — so a run is reproducible from the DB alone. Core stays overlay-agnostic (default hook returns `""`; empty provenance fields are omitted). For a multi-config Playwright suite (one config per lane — api-flow vs contrib vs portal), the overlay maps a spec to its `-c <config>` (and any other per-spec Playwright flags) via the `get_e2e_playwright_args(spec_path)` overlay hook; the `external` runner threads those into the `npx playwright test` command ahead of any explicit `--playwright-args` (default `[]` — no flags, prior command shape preserved). `t3 <overlay> e2e post-test-plan --manifest` ([#1409](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/1409)) maintains ONE structured test-plan note per **ticket** (never the MR), idempotent on a hidden marker carrying a JSON state blob (the merge SOT); each run merges its manifest's env(s) over the prior state, freezing the side it omits. The note renders a test plan — a multi-repo header with clickable commit-provenance and a `Dev ± Local` reconciliation, then per-workflow bodies in one of three templates (`capture-matrix` default side-by-side table, `browser-click-first` screenshots, `link-api` links + code; [#2304](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2304)). `--body-file` posts a pre-authored body verbatim (mutually exclusive with `--manifest`). Pure render/merge lives in `_test_plan_render`, host orchestration in `_test_plan`.
   - **Upload integrity.** Artifacts embed the relative `/uploads/<secret>/<file>` GitLab claims on save and upload to the project that owns the note's issue URL; a post-upload `verify_upload` gate re-fetches each via the token-authed API and magic-byte-checks it, so "posted" means "verified renderable" (`TestPlanMediaError` refuses otherwise).
   - **Image preflight** (`core/test_plan_validation`, before any upload): every image must carry a `highlightAndShoot` red box, none may be byte-identical (md5 dedup), and a manifest with no media is refused (`TestPlanValidationError`); `--skip-validation` is the user-only bypass.
   - **Honesty gates.** A colleague-repo body gate (`core/test_plan_blocked_gate`) refuses a `--body-file` post whose free text signals incomplete verification when the issue URL matches `colleague_repo_url_pattern` (`BlockedTestPlanPostError`); the structured `--manifest` render is exempt because its `**Blocked:** <reason>` disclosure is the honest channel. Self-evidence on the user's own ticket is un-gated by default (`post_e2e_evidence` in `on_behalf_auto_actions`, #960). `t3 <overlay> e2e retract-evidence` withdraws the note. A sibling field-context evidence probe (`core/doc_evidence`, [#2296](https://github.com/souliane/teatree/issues/2296)) asserts a generated-doc term in its expected structured field/column, never a page-wide substring — an available primitive, not yet a globally-wired gate.
